text: In a livestreamed talk ahead of #AliDay, Alibaba Group Chairman and CEO Daniel Zhang expressed thanks to employees and their loved ones for their efforts to weather the Covid-19 crisis.

This week's Alibaba News Roundup covers efforts to revitalize the economy after months of coronavirus-related disruptions. We also look at the reopening of Shanghai Disney and why picnics are getting more popular.
The @WHO's operations support & logistics chief talks about the importance of solidarity during the #COVID19 crisis.
An interview with John Caplan, @AlibabaB2B North America and Europe president, on how Alibaba’s online B2B marketplace helps US businesses during #Covid19.
The @DHSgov @IPRCenter acknowledged Alibaba's participation in and contributions to a public-private partnership formed to combat fraud and other illegal activity surrounding #Covid19.
See how Lazada's delivery riders get daily essentials to consumers, quickly and safely, during the #Covid19 lockdown in Malaysia.

http://Ele.me is a popular on-demand delivery platform in China. Users can get everything from food and groceries to even medicine brought to their doorsteps. During #Covid19, it ensured supplies reached housebound consumers across the country. http://alizi.la/37vfa8f

In a series highlighting small businesses that have made a positive social impact during #COVID19, @AlibabaB2B talks to a solopreneur artist who turned leftover fabric into masks for healthcare workers.

As daily life slowly returns to normal in China in the wake of #COVID19, Alibaba's entertainment platforms Damai and Youku announced an online concert series, “Believe in the Future,” to pay tribute to frontline medical workers and help boost morale. http://alizi.la/2KQud2k
From shopping coupons to flexible holiday packages, here are some of the efforts being undertaken to stimulate post-pandemic economic recovery in China.

The UN’s @WFP has exclusively tapped @OfficialCainiao to facilitate logistics for its new humanitarian hub in China. The hub will support global #COVID19 emergency response as well as the sourcing and shipment of medical supplies to affected regions worldwide.

Lazada Group CEO Pierre Poignant talks about the changes that #COVID19 has brought to the e-commerce landscape in Southeast Asia and the importance of building a digital economy for SMEs and consumers alike. Via @wwd

Alibaba Group founder @JackMa on why cooperation is key to combating #COVID19. He shared more insights at a recent livestreamed webinar co-hosted by @Foundation_Ma and @AfricaCDC. Read more: http://alizi.la/3aN7dvy

"Solidarity and collaboration are the only ways we can succeed," Alibaba Group founder @JackMa said at a livestreamed webinar co-hosted by @Foundation_Ma and the @AfricaCDC to share knowledge about Covid-19 solutions. Read more: http://alizi.la/3aN7dvy

An increase in online-delivery services – such as those offered by Freshippo, or Hema, in China – may present a way forward for American cities as they emerge from the coronavirus pandemic. via @TheAtlantic
Since the outbreak of #COVID19, Lazada has been working to provide support to businesses, consumers as well as local communities across Southeast Asia.
With its high level of interactivity and low threshold of entry, livestreaming has become an essential tool to help small merchants stay afloat during the #COVID19 pandemic. via @SCMPNews

Eco-friendly shoe brand @Allbirds had to brace for the changes brought on by #COVID19. Here's how the business leveraged technology and its omnichannel capabilities to continue sharing its message of sustainability and wellbeing during the pandemic.
.@alibaba_cloud invests $28 billion into its infrastructure in a bid to help businesses embrace digital technology and recover from coronavirus-related disruptions.
How fashion brand @MichaelKors is embracing digital to stay connected with consumers during the pandemic.
.@darazpk CEO Bjarke Mikkelsen talks about helping businesses and the economy in South Asia get back on track amid the pandemic.
Here’s how one company stepped up to help others and create positive social impact during the #COVID19 pandemic. #AlibabaBuildUp @AlibabaB2B

The Global MediXchange for Combating Covid-19 was set up to share medical insights and best practices for treating the coronavirus disease. To date, close to 3,000 healthcare workers from around the world have joined. Read more: http://alizi.la/GMCC
Supplies donated by @foundation_ma and Alibaba Foundation will be distributed by @WHO to help countries impacted by #COVID19.
Alibaba founder Jack Ma was named to the World's 25 Greatest Leaders list by @FortuneMagazine. This year's list is comprised of individuals who have "rallied the world" against the #coronavirus.
Alibaba Business School's GET Global Challenge empowers students to find digital solutions to help businesses, individuals and institutions during and after #COVID19.

Amid the ongoing coronavirus crisis, e-commerce platform Tmall said it would ramp up support for SMEs, starting with the goal of helping 1,000 emerging beauty brands achieve over $1.41 million each in sales in the coming year.
Christina Fontana, head of fashion and luxury for Tmall, shares tips on how brands can navigate the new e-commerce terrain and find opportunities amid Covid-19. via @mffashion_com
Gabby Hirata, @DVF's head of business development for Asia-Pacific, on how the fashion label has accelerated its digital strategy amid Covid-19.
How businesses can play a key role in helping society get through #COVID19 and in creating innovations that shape society after the crisis. via @ConversationEDU
Read about Alibaba’s companywide efforts to help small businesses during the coronavirus outbreak.

Alibaba’s Taobao Live platform is still the undisputed leader of commerce livestreams. In February, during the height of the coronavirus lockdown in China, the number of merchants on the Taobao livestreaming platform increased by 719%. via @glossyco

When coronavirus struck China hard, people were forced to stay at home for almost two months. Some brands turned to #livestream sales in China. It is the go-to option for young consumers seeking new products and discounts. via @Marketplace

We are excited to be part of One World: #TogetherAtHome – a special event that brings together some of the biggest names in music and comedy to support healthcare workers and the global effort to combat #COVID19. http://glblctzn.me/2xFbpj8

In light of the #Covid19 pandemic, Shanghai Fashion Week brought its entire roster of shows online — making it the world’s first fashion-week event at this scale to go fully digital. @Shanghai_FW https://alizi.la/2JJ6qRu
Learn more about Taobao Live’s plans to help more industries digitize their operations as well as @OfficialCainiao's logistics solutions amid the #COVID19 outbreak.

Cainiao has been partnering with close to 50 transportation and logistics partners and has thus far delivered over 100 million vital medical supplies to more than 140 countries and regions across the globe. @OfficialCainiao pledges to continue its #COVID19 relief efforts.

Cainiao's new chartered plane between the eWTP hubs of Hangzhou and Kuala Lumpur has made its inaugural flight. The dedicated cargo route will operate five flights weekly and play a key role in providing essential deliveries for #COVID19 relief in Malaysia. @OfficialCainiao

Taobao Live announced plans to help more than 200,000 retail stores make use of its platform this year. The livestreaming platform has become an increasingly important tool to help businesses continue operations during the ongoing coronavirus outbreak.

The first purely digital fashion week - the result of Shanghai Fashion Week’s online experiment in partnership with Tmall - provided valuable insights for brands and fashion week organizers to rethink their strategies amid the coronavirus outbreak.

Taobao Live announced plans to help more than 200,000 brick-and-mortar retail shops and 100 physical marketplaces make use of its livestreaming tools this year – a trend that's accelerated as more merchants impacted by COVID-19 turn to online platforms. (2/2)

Medical supplies have arrived in Myanmar, Mongolia and Laos. These are part of a wider donation made by the Jack Ma Foundation and Alibaba Foundation to support 23 Asian countries in the fight against the coronavirus outbreak. Read more: http://alizi.la/JMFAsia

Medical supplies have arrived in Nepal and Bangladesh. These were presented to the Ministry of Health and Population of Nepal and the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare of Bangladesh, respectively, to aid in the global fight against Covid-19. http://alizi.la/JMFAsia

The Alibaba Foundation and @Foundation_Ma are donating supplies to Azerbaijan, Bhutan, India, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Vietnam and Uzbekistan in the fight against Covid-19. The first batch has already been received by the Indian Red Cross Society in Delhi. http://alizi.la/JMFAsia

Covid-19 test kits donated by @Foundation_Ma and Alibaba Foundation have arrived in Phnom Penh, Cambodia. These were presented to Mam Bunheng, the country's health minister, in a ceremony also attended by the Chinese ambassador to Cambodia, Wang Wentian. http://alizi.la/JMFAsia
See how @Shanghai_FW is taking all of its runway shows online with Tmall, in light of #COVID19. #shfw #Day3

Medical items from @Foundation_Ma and Alibaba Foundation have been received by the Department of Health in the Philippines. According to the country's Finance Secretary, the supplies are critical to efforts to prevent the spread of the novel coronavirus. http://alizi.la/JMFAsia

Medical supplies have been making their way to countries across Asia as part of a joint effort by @Foundation_Ma and Alibaba Foundation to stem the spread of Covid-19 across all regions around the world. Click below to follow the latest developments.

Medical supplies arrived in Kuala Lumper last night and early this morning. These are among the first two batches of donations made by @Foundation_Ma and Alibaba Foundation to arrive in Malaysia as part of a larger global initiative to combat Covid-19. http://alizi.la/2UodUOB

To make the Covid-19 Prevention and Treatment Handbook more accessible to communities worldwide, it's been translated into French, Italian, Japanese, Spanish and Turkish. These are available alongside the Chinese and English editions. Read more: http://alizi.la/2w7wGlv

The first batch of masks, protective suits and face shields donated by @foundation_ma and Alibaba Foundation have landed in Bangkok's Suvarnabhumi Airport. These are part of a larger relief effort to help Asian countries fight against Covid-19. Read more: http://alizi.la/2UodUOB
We support the IOC's decision to postpone the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020 given the uncertainty surrounding the global coronavirus pandemic.
How Alibaba's Freshippo adapted to keep delivering in virus-hit China via @Reuters

Medical supplies donated by @foundation_ma and Alibaba Foundation made their way from China to Ethiopia, where they will be further distributed across the African continent. Together, we can overcome the global pandemic!

More than 6 million medical supplies donated by @foundation_ma and Alibaba Foundation have just arrived in Ethiopia and will make their way across Africa to communities impacted by Covid-19. Read more here: http://alizi.la/33t6ptV

This week’s News Roundup looks at cross-company efforts to further support the global company in the fight against the coronavirus pandemic. Click below to read more about worldwide donations, tech-based solutions and other efforts to combat Covid-19.
More than 78,000 people from 219 countries and regions have viewed the Covid-19 Prevention and Treatment Handbook. Download your copy: http://covid-19.alibabacloud.com

From a peer-communication platform that helps medical experts share knowledge to an epidemic-prediction tool, these new tech solutions from @alibaba_cloud are designed to support organizations worldwide in the fight against Covid-19.

@Alipay and MYBank launched a new initiative to offer low-interest loans and digital technologies for small business owners during #COVID19. Their goal: Support lending for 20% more store owners and, through Alipay’s digital tools, help them boost revenues by 20% this year.

@alibaba_cloud, DAMO Academy and DingTalk have joined forces to unveil a series of AI tech and cloud-based solutions to empower companies and organizations worldwide to fight against the coronavirus. Learn more here: http://alizi.la/2IUaFZY

Additional medical supplies donated by the @foundation_ma and Alibaba Foundation have landed in Liege. These will be delivered to medical staff in Belgium, France and Slovenia. For more on the foundations' coronavirus-relief efforts in Europe: http://alizi.la/JMFeurope

The Jack Ma Foundation and Alibaba Foundation have ramped up efforts to provide aid to European countries impacted by Covid-19. Click below to read about all the initiatives that have been carried out so far.

The Jack Ma Foundation and Alibaba Foundation announced the publication of a handbook detailing best practices from the First Affiliated Hospital, Zhejiang University School of Medicine, in treating Covid-19 patients.
@foundation_ma and Alibaba Foundation will donate 100,000 medical masks, 20,000 test kits and 1,000 protective suits to each of the 54 nations on the African continent.

Belgium, which joined the Electronic World Trade Platform in 2018, has been working closely with @foundation_ma and the Alibaba Foundation to facilitate the distribution and delivery of medical supplies amid the coronavirus outbreak.
An expert from Alibaba Group’s research and innovation institute explains how a new AI tool can diagnose Covid-19 in 20 seconds with 96% accuracy.
This week, we look at the Jack Ma Foundation’s coronavirus-relief efforts, Shanghai Fashion Week’s latest announcement and how pigs are winning over the hearts of viewers on livestreaming channels.

In a series highlighting the stories of inspirational women in the Alibaba ecosystem, we speak to Shang Xinyuan, a mother of two and an http://Ele.me delivery worker who has helped keep supplies flowing in the city of Shenzhen during the virus.

The Jack Ma Foundation signed an agreement with @TheDohertyInst to fund the development of treatments for the Covid-19 virus. The donation is part of an ongoing commitment from the foundation to find solutions to the health crisis.
From exercise role-playing games to learning DIY haircutting through online tutorials, here's how Chinese consumers are making the most of their time at home during the coronavirus outbreak.
A new report by Alibaba think tank @Luohan_Academy sheds light on the enduring entrepreneurial spirit of the small-business sector in China, which has been hardest hit by the coronavirus outbreak.

For merchants across different industries, livestreaming has become an important tool not only to offset the decline in offline business during the coronavirus, but also to encourage creativity in marketing and customer engagement.
A growing number of farmers are looking for innovative ways to ensure fresh produce from village farms still makes it to consumer tables during the coronavirus outbreak.
Alibaba Group is leveraging its key cloud-based technologies and platforms, such as DingTalk, to help prevent the spread of the Covid-19 virus.

Alibaba Group unveiled 20 measures to help SMEs in China affected by the coronavirus outbreak. The measures range from waived platform fees and interest-free loans to subsidized services and increased logistics efficiency. Read more below.

The Alibaba Global Direct Sourcing Platform has been introduced to connect sellers of medical supplies directly with hospitals and local authorities in China most affected by the novel coronavirus. Read how the initiative is helping afflicted communities.
Alibaba Group's logistics arm, @OfficialCainiao, launched its "Green Channel" initiative to expedite the delivery of medical-aid donations to areas hit by the coronavirus outbreak.

#Cainiao launched its Green Channel initiative to bring medical supplies to areas hit by the coronavirus outbreak. Since last week, the initiative has delivered more than 5 million masks, 7,000 cases of disinfectant fluid and 40 tons of food to affected communities.
